1. Describe Project
A: It's an end to end production style application on AWS where i deployed a dockerized flask application on ec2, configured nginx as reverse proxy, placed it
   behind application load balancer, added auto scaling group, monitoring using cloud watch and setup sns notification and added the logs and configuration files
   to s3 bucket for backup. In this project i gained experience on Linux, aws services, docker, git, monitoring

2. Explain more about project step by step
A: Its an aws production style flask application
   1. I launched an ec2, cloned the project from github and installed docker and ran docker to convert the docker file to docker image and then ran the application in
      docker container
   2. Instead of exposing flask directly to users, i configured nginx as reverse proxy , so now nginx listens on port 80, forwards request to flask application on port
      5000 
   3. To have distributed traffic, i created ami of the ec2, launched a second ec2 using that ami and then i added load balancers to the both ec2's.
   4. To handle high traffic, i also added auto scaling group
   5. For monitoring i installed cloud watch agent in ec2 to collect the monitoring metrics from ec2 and then send to aws cloud watch
   6. I configured sns, cloud watch alarms to get cloud watch alarms when something exceeds the limit
   7. Finally i created encrypted and versioned s3 bucket and stored backup of configuration and log files

